 Given my cautious nature, I would prefer to maintain some degree of security and predictability. In this game, choosing 'R' twice consecutively with an anonymous player might not be advantageous because the payoff is only 45$ after 75 rounds if they also choose 'R'. However, if they choose 'B', I get 0$.

On the other hand, if I consistently pick 'B', I can expect a more stable payout of 12$ per round. This might not be as high as the 45$ I could potentially earn with 'R' if my partner also chooses 'R', but it is less risky and provides a more predictable outcome.

Therefore, considering my moderately cautious nature, I would choose 'B' for this game. {B}
